### Write consistency factor

The `write_consistency_factor` represents the number of replicas that must acknowledge a write operation before responding to the client. It is set to 1 by default. It can be configured at the collections creation or when updating the collection parameters.

This value can range from 1 to the number of replicas you have for each shard.

```http
PUT /collections/{collection_name}
{
    "vectors": {
        "size": 300,
        "distance": "Cosine"
    },
    "shard_number": 6,
    "replication_factor": 2,
    "write_consistency_factor": 2
}
```

